### Account A (S3 Only)
Create the S3 Bucket:

Go to S3 > Create bucket.

Name: my-terraform-tftate (must be globally unique).

Region: Select your region (e.g., ap-south-1).

Versioning: Enable (Highly recommended for state recovery).

Create the Cross-Account IAM Role:

Go to IAM > Roles > Create role.

Select Custom trust policy and paste this:

JSON
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [{
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": { "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::ACCOUNT_B_ID:root" },
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole"
  }]
}


Permissions: Attach an inline policy to this role:

JSON
{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [{
        "Effect": "Allow",
        "Action": [
            "s3:ListBucket",
            "s3:GetObject",
            "s3:PutObject",
            "s3:DeleteObject"
        ],
        "Resource": [
            "arn:aws:s3:::my-company-terraform-state",
            "arn:aws:s3:::my-company-terraform-state/*"
        ]
    }]
}
Role Name: CrossAccountStateRole.



### account B
Go to IAM > Identity Providers > Add provider.

Select OpenID Connect.

Provider URL: https://token.actions.githubusercontent.com

Audience: sts.amazonaws.com

After creating the provider, click Assign role > Create new role.

Trust Policy: 

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "Federated": "arn:aws:iam::ACCOUNT_B_ID:oidc-provider/token.actions.githubusercontent.com"
      },
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity",
      "Condition": {
        "StringLike": {
          "token.actions.githubusercontent.com:sub": "repo:abhishek095859/demo-poc:*"
        },
        "StringEquals": {
          "token.actions.githubusercontent.com:aud": "sts.amazonaws.com"
        }
      }
    }
  ]
}


create a role 

